      "\n  have h₁ : ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound x y\n  have h₂ : (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ :=\n    by\n      apply ComplexRMK.variation_univ_le_norm\n      <;>\n      (try simp_all) <;>\n      (try norm_num) <;>\n      (try linarith) <;>\n      (try exact ⟨by continuity, by continuity⟩) <;>\n      (try\n        {\n          refine' IsBoundedMap.mk (1 : ℝ) _\n          intro f\n          simp_all [continuousLinearMap_norm_le]\n          <;>\n          (try norm_num) <;>\n          (try linarith)\n        }\n      )\n  calc\n    (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := h₂\n    _ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := h₁\n    _ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n      have h₃ : (‖x‖ : ℝ) ≤ ‖x‖ₑ := by simp [norm_rel, ENNReal.ofReal_le]\n      have h₄ : (‖y‖ : ℝ) ≤ ‖y‖ₑ := by simp [norm_rel, ENNReal.ofReal_le]\n      have h₅ : (‖x‖ * ‖y‖ : ℝ) ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n        calc\n          (‖x‖ * ‖y‖ : ℝ) ≤ (‖x‖ₑ : ℝ) * (‖y‖ : ℝ) := by gcongr <;> simp_all\n          _ ≤ (‖x‖ₑ : ℝ) * (‖y‖ₑ : ℝ) := by gcongr <;> simp_all\n          _ = ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by norm_cast\n      exact_mod_cast h₅",
      "\n  have h₁ : (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ =\n      (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).norm := by\n    rw [Real.norm_eq_abs Complex.abs.nonneg]\n    <;> simp [Complex.norm_eq_abs]\n    <;>\n    (try simp_all [Complex.abs, Complex.normSq, Real.sqrt_le_iff]) <;>\n    (try norm_num) <;>\n    (try simp_all [Real.sqrt_le_iff]) <;>\n    (try linarith) <;>\n    (try ring_nf) <;>\n    (try field_simp [Complex.abs, Complex.normSq]) <;>\n    (try norm_num) <;>\n    (try simp_all [Real.sqrt_le_iff]) <;>\n    (try linarith)\n  rw [h₁]\n  have h₂ : ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y)‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := by\n    -- Use the fact that the operator norm of the measure is bounded by ‖x‖ * ‖y‖\n    have h₃ : ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := by\n      -- Use the previously established bound on the linear functional\n      have h₄ : ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound x y\n      -- The norm of the measure is bounded by the norm of the linear functional\n      have h₅ : ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by\n        -- Use the property of the Riesz representation theorem\n        have h₆ : ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by\n          -- The norm of the measure is less than or equal to the norm of the linear functional\n          calc\n            ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ =\n                ‖ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure _‖ := rfl\n            _ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by\n              -- Use the fact that the norm of the measure is less than or equal to the norm of the linear functional\n              have h₇ : ‖(ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure (compSL C₀((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) ℂ _ _ (cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y) (@ZeroAtInftyContinuousMap.ContinuousMap.liftZeroAtInftyCLE (spectrum ℂ a) ℂ ℂ _ _ _ _ _ _).symm.toContinuousLinearMap) : C₀((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by\n                -- Use the property of the Riesz representation theorem\n                apply ComplexRMK.le_norm_rieszMeasure\n              simpa using h₇\n        exact h₆\n      -- Combine the inequalities\n      calc\n        ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := h₅\n        _ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := h₄\n    -- The norm of the measure is bounded by ‖x‖ * ‖y‖\n    simpa using h₃\n  -- Convert the norm of the measure to the variation of the measure\n  have h₃ : ‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y)‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := h₂\n  have h₄ : (‖x‖ : ℝ) * ‖y‖ = ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n    simp [norm_eq_abs, Complex.abs, Complex.normSq]\n    <;> ring_nf\n    <;> field_simp [Real.sqrt_eq_iff_sq_eq]\n    <;> ring_nf\n    <;> norm_num\n    <;> linarith [norm_nonneg x, norm_nonneg y]\n  -- Combine the inequalities to get the final result\n  have h₅ : (‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y)‖ : ℝ) ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n    calc\n      (‖(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y)‖ : ℝ) ≤ (‖x‖ * ‖y‖ : ℝ) := by exact_mod_cast h₃\n      _ = (‖x‖ : ℝ) * (‖y‖ : ℝ) := by norm_cast\n      _ = ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n        simp [h₄]\n  exact_mod_cast h₅",
      "₁",
      "\n  have h₁ : (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ = ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by\n    rw [show (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y : VectorMeasure _ _) = (ComplexRiesz\n      (compSL C₀((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) ℂ _ _ (cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y)\n        (@ZeroAtInftyContinuousMap.ContinuousMap.liftZeroAtInftyCLE\n          (spectrum ℂ a) ℂ ℂ _ _ _ _ _ _).symm.toContinuousLinearMap)) by rfl]\n    <;> simp [ComplexRiesz.rieszMeasure, MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.toVectorMeasure_coe,\n      VectorMeasure.variation, ContinuousLinearMap.norm_def]\n    <;> simp_all [Real.norm_eq_abs]\n    <;> congr\n    <;> ext\n    <;> simp_all [C0.coeff]\n    <;> ring_nf\n    <;> simp_all [C0.coeff]\n    <;> field_simp [Real.norm_eq_abs]\n    <;> simp_all [norm_smul, abs_of_nonneg]\n    <;> linarith [Metric_space_norm_nonneg x, Metric_space_norm_nonneg y]\n  \n  have h₂ : ‖(cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) →L[ℂ] ℂ)‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := by\n    apply ContinuousLinearMap.opNorm_le_bound\n    · positivity\n    · intro f\n      simp only [cfc_toLinearFunctional_apply]\n      calc\n        ‖⟪x, ((cfcHom (IsSelfAdjoint.isStarNormal ha)) f) y⟫_ℂ‖\n          ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖((cfcHom (IsSelfAdjoint.isStarNormal ha)) f) y‖ := norm_inner_le_norm x\n            (((cfcHom (IsSelfAdjoint.isStarNormal ha)) f) y)\n        _ ≤ ‖x‖ * (‖((cfcHom (IsSelfAdjoint.isStarNormal ha)) f)‖ * ‖y‖) :=\n          mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_left (le_opNorm ((cfcHom (IsSelfAdjoint.isStarNormal ha)) f) y)\n            (norm_nonneg x)\n        _ = ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ * ‖((cfcHom (IsSelfAdjoint.isStarNormal ha)) f)‖ := by ring\n        _ = ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ * ‖f‖ := by rw [norm_cfcHom a f]\n        _ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ * ‖f‖ := by simp\n  \n  have h₃ : (‖x‖ * ‖y‖ : ℝ≥0∞) ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n    have h₃₁ : (‖x‖ : ℝ≥0∞) = ‖x‖ₑ := by\n      simp [norm_eq_abs, ENNReal.ofReal_eq_coe]\n      <;> simp_all [Real.norm_eq_abs]\n      <;> norm_cast\n      <;> simp [Real.norm_eq_abs]\n      <;> norm_cast\n    have h₃₂ : (‖y‖ : ℝ≥0∞) = ‖y‖ₑ := by\n      simp [norm_eq_abs, ENNReal.ofReal_eq_coe]\n      <;> simp_all [Real.norm_eq_abs]\n      <;> norm_cast\n      <;> simp [Real.norm_eq_abs]\n      <;> norm_cast\n    calc\n      (‖x‖ * ‖y‖ : ℝ≥0∞) = (‖x‖ : ℝ≥0∞) * (‖y‖ : ℝ≥0∞) := by norm_cast\n      _ = ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by rw [h₃₁, h₃₂]\n      _ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := le_refl _\n  \n  have h₄ : (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n    calc\n      (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ = ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by rw [h₁]\n      _ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := h₂\n      _ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n        exact le_trans (by norm_cast) h₃\n  \n  exact h₄",
      "\n     fun f g ↦ ⟨fun x ↦ g (f x), ...⟩\n   ```\n\n   Therefore, in `compSL C₀(σ(a)) C(σ(a)) ℂ ...`, we need `(C₀(σ(a)) →L[ℂ]",
      "\n  have h₁ : ‖x‖ₛ * ‖y‖ₛ = ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := by\n    simp [norm_eq_abs]\n    <;> ring_nf\n    <;> field_simp [Complex.abs_of_nonneg, Complex.normSq_nonneg, Real.sqrt_nonneg]\n    <;> ring_nf\n  have h₂ : (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := by\n    have h₃ : ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound x y\n    calc\n      (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ =\n          ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure (compSL C₀((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ) ℂ _ _ (cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y)\n          (ZeroAtInftyContinuousMap.ContinuousMap.liftZeroAtInftyCLE (spectrum ℂ a) ℂ ℂ _ _ _ _ _ _).symm.toContinuousLinearMap)\n        .variation Set.univ := rfl\n      _ ≤ ‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ := by\n        apply ComplexRieszMeasure.rieszMeasure_Variation_le\n      _ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := h₃\n  calc\n    (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ := h₂\n    _ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by\n      have h₃ : ‖x‖ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ := by\n        exact hestia_convergent_bounded_norm_le m (λ n, ‖x n‖ : ℕ → ℝ) ‖x‖ _ _ _ _ <;> norm_num\n      have h₄ : ‖y‖ ≤ ‖y‖ₑ := by\n        exact hestia_convergent_bounded_norm_le m (λ n, ‖y n‖ : ℕ → ℝ) ‖y‖ _ _ _ _ <;> norm_num\n      calc\n        ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ := by gcongr\n        _ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by gcongr\n  <;>\n  norm_num",
      "Riesz–Markov–Kakutani, we have that if `φ` is a continuous linear functional on `C(σ, ℂ)`, then there exists a unique complex measure `μ` such that `φ(f) = ∫ f dμ`, and `‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖`.\n\nBut in Lean, `ComplexM勐H.rieszMeasure` (whatever it is) should provide the measure `μ`, and perhaps the norm of `μ` is equal to the norm of `φ`.\n\nBut looking back:\n\nWe have `ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure (compSL ...)`.\n\nBut we don't know what that does. Perhaps it is supposed to be the classical measure, but it uses `ZeroAtInfty`?\n\nMoreover, perhaps that lemma is not actually constructing `μ` with `‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖`, but just giving us some `μ`, and perhaps we need to know more. \n\nBut perhaps `ComplexM勐H.rieszMeasure` actually constructs `μ` so that `‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖`.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps the theorem is using `ComplexM勐H.rieszMeasure` to get `μ`, and then `μ.variation Set.univ = ‖φ‖`, because `‖φ‖` is the smallest bound for `|φ(f)|`, and similarly `μ.variation Set.univ` is the smallest bound for `|∫ f dμ|`, and when `φ(f) = ∫ f dμ`, then indeed `‖φ‖ = ‖μ‖`.\n\nBut perhaps it is so, but we'd need to know that.\n\nBut perhaps the `ComplexM勐H.rieszMeasure` provides that.\n\nGiven that we can't see the `ComplexM勐H` module, we might not have that formalized.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps the statement is just that `μ.variation Set.univ ≤ ‖φ‖`.\n\nBut the problem requires `μ.variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.\n\nBut `‖φ‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖` is already from `cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound`.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps `ComplexM勐H.rieszMeasure` has that `‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖`, and hence `μ.variation Set.univ = ‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.\n\nBut then we need to have that `‖φ‖ = ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`, but perhaps not, just `‖φ‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps we have `‖μ‖ ≤ ‖φ‖`, and hence `μ.variation Set.univ ≤ ‖φ‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.\n\nBut I think the most plausible things are:\n\n1. In Lean, `‖x‖ₑ = ENNReal.ofReal ‖x‖`, and we have to identify `ComplexM勐H` sufficiently, and then use the fact that `‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖`, and so `μ.variation Set.univ = ‖φ‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`, then convert `‖x‖ * ‖y‖ : ℝ` to `ℝ≥0∞`.\n\nBut I think that perhaps there was a misunderstanding, and perhaps the actual plan was:\n\n1. Use the previous bound on `‖cfc_toLinearFunctional x y‖`, and then some general theorem that `‖μ‖ = ‖φ‖` to conclude that `μ.variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.\n\nBut because in Lean, the goal is `μ.variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ`, perhaps we should have `‖x‖ₑ = ENNReal.ofReal ‖x‖`.\n\nBut perhaps, since in Lean, we have not the definition, we can instead try to find a proof that works assuming `‖x‖ₑ = ENNReal.ofReal ‖x‖`, and then perhaps later the user",
